cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as event extraction. It may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it proposes a novel neural model for the task. Additionally, it involves information retrieval (IR) techniques for collecting and annotating the dataset, which makes cs.IR a likely sub-category. Finally, the use of latent variable models suggests that it may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
